/-! ## 1. (a) The conserved coverage floor caps the collective solving rate.

We model the civilization's collective problem-solving STOCK by the conserved
subdomain-mass average intervention count
`NŐĄ := ‚ąĎ_a (cw p_X a)¬∑N_a` of the R6_Agent6 tower. The R.352 solving rate is
`őľ_N = W / NŐĄ`. The conserved coverage floor `ő¶‚āÄ/log(cardMmax) ‚Č§ NŐĄ`
(R6_Agent6 `conserved_mixture_fano_floor`) ‚ÄĒ whose normalisation is GENERATED
by T.18.10 conservation ‚ÄĒ places a hard CEILING on `őľ_N`. -/

/-- **(a-core) A positive coverage floor on `NŐĄ` caps `W/NŐĄ` from above.**

Pure-order kernel feeding the sociology rate: if the collective intervention
stock `Nbar` satisfies the (strictly positive) coverage floor `0 < floor ‚Č§ Nbar`
and `0 ‚Č§ W`, then the solving rate `W / Nbar` is capped by `W / floor`. -/
theorem solving_rate_ceiling_of_floor
    (W Nbar floor : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hW : 0 ‚Č§ W) (hfloor_pos : 0 < floor) (hfloor : floor ‚Č§ Nbar) :
    W / Nbar ‚Č§ W / floor := by
  have hNbar_pos : 0 < Nbar := lt_of_lt_of_le hfloor_pos hfloor
  exact div_le_div_of_nonneg_left hW hfloor_pos hfloor

/-- **(a) Conserved coverage floor ‚üĻ collective solving-rate ceiling.**

Take the collective intervention stock to be the conserved subdomain-mass
average `NŐĄ = ‚ąĎ_a (cw p_X a)¬∑N_a` of the R6_Agent6 tower (its normalisation
`‚ąĎ cw = 1` GENERATED by T.18.10 conservation). The R6_Agent6 coverage floor
`ő¶‚āÄ/log(cardMmax) ‚Č§ NŐĄ` together with `ő¶‚āÄ > 0` (so the floor is strictly
positive) caps the R.352 solving rate `őľ_N = W / NŐĄ`:

    őľ_N = W / NŐĄ  ‚Č§  W ¬∑ (ő¶‚āÄ/log(cardMmax))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ  =  W ¬∑ log(cardMmax) / ő¶‚āÄ .

The conserved coverage floor is a binding ceiling on the collective solving
rate ‚ÄĒ no education allocation can break the information-theoretic cap. -/
theorem collective_solving_rate_ceiling
    {ő© : Type} [Fintype ő©] [DecidableEq ő©]
    (p_X : ő© ‚Üí NNReal)
    (h_norm : ‚ąĎ ŌČ, p_X ŌČ = 1)
    (parts : Finset (Finset ő©))
    (h_disjoint : ‚ąÄ S ‚ąą parts, ‚ąÄ T ‚ąą parts, S ‚Č† T ‚Üí Disjoint S T)
    (h_cover : ‚ąÄ ŌČ, ‚ąÉ S ‚ąą parts,
        ŌČ ‚ąą S)
    (N logCardM :
        R6_Agent6_FanoFloorFromConservationGenerator.Committee parts ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (W Phi0 cardMmax : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hW : 0 ‚Č§ W)
    (hN_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ N a)
    (hcap_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ logCardM a)
    (hPhi0 : 0 < Phi0)
    (hcardMmax : 1 < cardMmax)
    (hcap_le : ‚ąÄ a, logCardM a ‚Č§ Real.log cardMmax)
    (hfano : ‚ąÄ a, Phi0 ‚Č§ N a * logCardM a) :
    let Nbar := ‚ąĎ a : R6_Agent6_FanoFloorFromConservationGenerator.Committee parts,
        R6_Agent6_FanoFloorFromConservationGenerator.cw p_X a * N a
    W / Nbar ‚Č§ W / (Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax) := by
  intro Nbar
  -- R6_Agent6 conserved coverage floor on the conserved mixture average.
  have hfloor :
      Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax ‚Č§ Nbar :=
    R6_Agent6_FanoFloorFromConservationGenerator.conserved_mixture_fano_floor
      p_X h_norm parts h_disjoint h_cover N logCardM Phi0 cardMmax
      hN_nonneg hcap_nonneg hcardMmax hcap_le hfano
  -- The floor is strictly positive: ő¶‚āÄ > 0 and log(cardMmax) > 0.
  have hlog_pos : 0 < Real.log cardMmax := Real.log_pos hcardMmax
  have hfloor_pos : 0 < Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax := div_pos hPhi0 hlog_pos
  exact solving_rate_ceiling_of_floor W Nbar (Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax)
    hW hfloor_pos hfloor

/-! ## 2. The phase boundary (R.352).

The R.352 order parameter is `őľ_N ‚ąí őĽ_P`. By `R_352_net_rate_sign` the sign of
the order parameter is the sign of `exp((őĪ‚ąíő≥)t) ‚ąí őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ`; the BOUNDARY is the
locus `őľ_N = őĽ_P`, equivalently `exp((őĪ‚ąíő≥)t) = őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ`, attained at the
crossing time `t* = log(őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ)/(őĪ‚ąíő≥)` (`R_352_transition_time`). -/

/-- **(phase boundary) At the crossing time the order parameter vanishes.**

The R.352 crossing time `t* = log(őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ)/(őĪ‚ąíő≥)` (with `őĪ ‚Č† ő≥` and
`őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ > 0`) realises the phase boundary: it solves the boundary equation
`exp((őĪ‚ąíő≥)t*) = őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ` (R.352 `R_352_transition_time`). Combined with the
order-parameter sign law (R.352 `R_352_net_rate_sign`), at `t*` the rates
satisfy `őľ_N(t*) ‚Č§ őĽ_P(t*)` AND `őĽ_P(t*) ‚Č§ őľ_N(t*)` are simultaneously NOT both
strict ‚ÄĒ i.e. the strict inequality `őľ_N > őĽ_P` FAILS at `t*` (boundary, not
interior of the active phase). We package the boundary as: `őľ_N(t*) > őĽ_P(t*)`
is FALSE, witnessing that `t*` is the phase boundary rather than the active
phase. -/
theorem optimum_at_phase_boundary
    (W0 N0 lam0 őĪ_eff ő≥ : ‚ĄĚ)
    (h_N0_pos : 0 < N0) (h_lam0_pos : 0 < lam0) (h_W0_pos : 0 < W0)
    (h_ne : őĪ_eff - ő≥ ‚Č† 0) :
    let tstar := Real.log (lam0 * N0 / W0) / (őĪ_eff - ő≥)
    ¬¨ (R352_CivilizationPhase.muN W0 N0 őĪ_eff tstar
        > R352_CivilizationPhase.lamP lam0 ő≥ tstar) := by
  intro tstar
  -- őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ > 0.
  have hpos : 0 < lam0 * N0 / W0 := by positivity
  -- R.352 crossing time: exp((őĪ‚ąíő≥)t*) = őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ, so it is NOT > őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ.
  have hcross :
      Real.exp ((őĪ_eff - ő≥) * tstar) = lam0 * N0 / W0 :=
    R352_CivilizationPhase.R_352_transition_time W0 N0 lam0 őĪ_eff ő≥ hpos h_ne
  -- R.352 order-parameter sign law: őľ_N > őĽ_P ‚ÜĒ exp((őĪ‚ąíő≥)t*) > őĽ‚āÄN‚āÄ/W‚āÄ.
  have hsign :
      R352_CivilizationPhase.muN W0 N0 őĪ_eff tstar
        > R352_CivilizationPhase.lamP lam0 ő≥ tstar
      ‚ÜĒ Real.exp ((őĪ_eff - ő≥) * tstar) > lam0 * N0 / W0 :=
    R352_CivilizationPhase.R_352_net_rate_sign W0 N0 lam0 őĪ_eff ő≥ tstar
      h_N0_pos h_lam0_pos h_W0_pos
  -- At the boundary the strict order-parameter inequality fails.
  rw [hsign, hcross]
  exact lt_irrefl _

/-! ## 3. The optimal education allocation (R.350 ‚ąė R.62).

In the `|K_A| ‚Čę |K_H|` limit the KKT corner kills the two knowledge dimensions
(R.350 `R_350_both_knowledge_corners`), the budget collapses to `c_Z + c_őļ = C`
(R.350 `R_350_budget_residual`), and the surviving marginals balance ‚ÄĒ either
abstractly (R.350 `R_350_marginal_balance`) or via the R.62 divide-by-cost
identity (R.62 `R_62_pairwise_marginal_equality`). -/

/-- **(allocation) Optimal education allocation: corner + budget + balance.**

Bundling R.350 and R.62: in the high-coverage limit (`‚ąāE[N]/‚ąāc_K, ‚ąāE[N]/‚ąāc_H ‚Č§ 0`,
multiplier `őĽ > 0`) with the KKT verdicts on each knowledge dimension, the
optimal allocation
  * kills the knowledge dimensions `c_K* = 0 ‚ąß c_H* = 0` (R.350 corner);
  * collapses the budget to `c_Z + c_őļ = C` (R.350 budget residual);
  * balances the surviving cost-normalised marginals `‚ąāN/‚ąāc_Z = ‚ąāN/‚ąāc_őļ`
    (R.350 marginal balance) AND, with unit costs `c_Z' = c_őļ' = 1`, the R.62
    divide-by-cost identity `(‚ąāN/‚ąāc_Z)/c_Z' = (‚ąāN/‚ąāc_őļ)/c_őļ'`. -/
theorem optimal_education_allocation
    (dEN_dcK dEN_dcH lam cK_star cH_star : ‚ĄĚ)
    (dEN_dcZ dEN_dcőļ : ‚ĄĚ) (cZ cőļ C : ‚ĄĚ)
    (h_mK : dEN_dcK ‚Č§ 0) (h_mH : dEN_dcH ‚Č§ 0) (h_lam_pos : 0 < lam)
    (h_bdK : cK_star = 0 ‚ą® dEN_dcK = lam)
    (h_bdH : cH_star = 0 ‚ą® dEN_dcH = lam)
    (h_budget : cK_star + cZ + cH_star + cőļ = C)
    (h_stat_Z : dEN_dcZ = lam * 1) (h_stat_őļ : dEN_dcőļ = lam * 1) :
    -- corner solution
    (cK_star = 0 ‚ąß cH_star = 0)
    -- budget residual
    ‚ąß (cZ + cőļ = C)
    -- abstract marginal balance (R.350)
    ‚ąß (dEN_dcZ = dEN_dcőļ)
    -- R.62 cost-normalised marginal equality (unit costs)
    ‚ąß (dEN_dcZ / 1 = dEN_dcőļ / 1) := by
  -- R.350 corner: both knowledge dimensions vanish.
  have hcorner : cK_star = 0 ‚ąß cH_star = 0 :=
    R350_EduOptimalAllocation.R_350_both_knowledge_corners
      dEN_dcK dEN_dcH lam cK_star cH_star h_mK h_mH h_lam_pos h_bdK h_bdH
  refine ‚ü®hcorner, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ -- R.350 budget residual.
    exact R350_EduOptimalAllocation.R_350_budget_residual
      cK_star cZ cH_star cőļ C h_budget hcorner.1 hcorner.2
  ¬∑ -- R.350 abstract marginal balance.
    exact R350_EduOptimalAllocation.R_350_marginal_balance
      dEN_dcZ dEN_dcőļ lam h_stat_Z h_stat_őļ
  ¬∑ -- R.62 divide-by-cost equality with unit costs c_Z' = c_őļ' = 1.
    exact KKTMarginalEquality.R_62_pairwise_marginal_equality
      dEN_dcZ dEN_dcőļ 1 1 lam one_ne_zero one_ne_zero h_stat_Z h_stat_őļ

